      "id": "behavioral-health",
      "name": "Behavioral health access (mental health and substance use)",
      "memberVoice": "I'm struggling and I don't know who to call or whether Medi-Cal even covers therapy - so I just keep suffering.",
      "description": "Members often do not know how to reach mental health or substance use care, or which door to use. In LA County, mild-to-moderate mental health services are usually handled through your Medi-Cal managed-care plan, while specialty (more serious) mental health services and crisis services are provided through the LA County Department of Mental Health (DMH) Help Line, which operates 24/7. Substance use services are also accessible through county lines. Stigma, language, and not knowing the entry point are major barriers, and crisis support like 988 and the Crisis Text Line is available immediately.",
