      "id": "plan-choice-enrollment",
      "name": "Confusing plan choice and enrollment (Health Care Options)",
      "memberVoice": "I got a form asking me to pick a health plan and I have no idea which one is right for me or what happens if I do nothing.",
      "description": "New LA County Medi-Cal members receive a Medi-Cal Choice Form from Health Care Options (HCO) and must pick a managed-care plan. The choices, networks, and deadlines are confusing, and if a member does nothing they may be auto-assigned to a plan that does not include their doctor. Members can choose or change their plan at any time by phone or online through HCO, and aligning the plan with their existing doctor or preferred clinic is key. Navigators can walk members through which plan includes their providers before they choose.",
